==English==
===Etymology===
Named after [[physician]] [[w:Henry Heimlich|Henry Heimlich]] who described the procedure in 1974.  Edward A. Patrick asserts that he was co-developer of it.
[[Category:English eponyms]]
===Proper noun===
# A [[first aid]] procedure used to treat [[choke|choking]].  The [[patient]] is [[lift]]ed from behind, squeezing their [[diaphram]] to [[expel]] air and thereby [[dislodge|dislodging]] an [[obstruction]] in the [[windpipe]].
[[Category:Medicine]]